Durban - In commemoration of World Children's Day, which takes place in November, King Edward VIII Hospital, in partnership with the Lamees Ryan Foundation, hosted a Christmas party for 50 underprivileged special needs children at the hospital's Jubilee Hall on Thursday.
The Lamees Ryan Foundation was founded after three-year-old Lamees - who was diagnosed with cerebral palsy, among other disabilities - died in 2016.

Natasha Ryan, the grandmother of Lamees and founder of the foundation, said that when her granddaughter was in King Edward VIII Hospital, her family saw the challenges children with disabilities face daily.
“Because my granddaughter had such an impact on our lives, we decided to help other children and make a difference in their lives,” said Ryan.


 







